  "Question": "<p>I know that my reasoning is incorrect, I just don't know where I went wrong. I did discuss this with my Maths teacher, and even she could not find what I did wrong.</p> <p>Let us begin by assuming a function, <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_798\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"f(x)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>f</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> that is continuous and has an antiderivative in the interval <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_799\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"[0,2\\pi]\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo>,</mo> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>\u03c0</mi> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo> </mrow> </math></span>. Let <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_800\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"A\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>A</mi> </math></span> be the area under the curve for <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_801\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"f(x)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>f</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> in the interval <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_802\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"[0,2\\pi]\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo>,</mo> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>\u03c0</mi> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_803\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"A=\\displaystyle\\int_{0}^{2\\pi}{f(x)\\mathrm{d}x}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>A</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <msubsup> <mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>\u03c0</mi> </mrow> </msubsup> <mrow> <mi>f</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo>d</mo> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p>Now there must exist a function, <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_804\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"g(x)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>g</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> such that:  </p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_805\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"f(x)=g(x)\\cdot\\cos(x)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>f</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>g</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>\u22c5</mo> <mrow> <mi>cos</mi> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p>Substituting the value of <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_806\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"f(x)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>f</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>:</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_807\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"A=\\displaystyle\\int_{0}^{2\\pi}{g(x)\\cdot\\cos(x)\\mathrm{d}x}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>A</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <msubsup> <mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>\u03c0</mi> </mrow> </msubsup> <mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>g</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>\u22c5</mo> <mrow> <mi>cos</mi> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo>d</mo> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p>Using t substitution:<br/> Let <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_808\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"t=\\sin(x)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>t</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mi>sin</mi> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span><br/> Then: <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_809\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\mathrm{d}t=\\cos(x)\\mathrm{d}x\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>t</mi> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>cos</mi> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span><br/> And:  <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_810\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"x=\\arcsin(t)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mi>arcsin</mi> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>t</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p>Changing the limits:<br/> <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_811\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"t=\\sin(x)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>t</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mi>sin</mi> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span><br/> <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_812\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mn>0</mn> </math></span> becomes <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_813\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\sin(0)=0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>sin</mi> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </math></span><br/> <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_814\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"2\\pi\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>\u03c0</mi> </mrow> </math></span> becomes <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_815\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\sin(2\\pi)=0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>sin</mi> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>\u03c0</mi> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p>Substituting in the definite integral:</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_816\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"A=\\displaystyle\\int_{0}^{0}{g(\\arcsin(t))\\mathrm{d}t}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>A</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <msubsup> <mo largeop=\"true\" symmetric=\"true\">\u222b</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mn>0</mn> </msubsup> <mrow> <mi>g</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mi>arcsin</mi> <mo>\u2061</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>t</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo>d</mo> <mi>t</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p>But Definite Integral where the lower and upper bounds are the same is <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_817\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mn>0</mn> </math></span>.<br/> So:</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_818\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"A=0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>A</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </math></span>, which is not possible.</p> <p>Thanks for the help.</p>",
